# DoomViz CI plan: build, test, release on GitHub Actions

## Goals

- Every push and PR runs the full test suite on a clean macOS Apple Silicon runner.
- Three test tiers: unit, integration, end-to-end (visual regression).
- VRT snapshots and diffs persist as downloadable build artifacts; pass/fail surfaces as a GitHub Check on the PR.
- Tagged releases produce a signed + notarized + stapled VST3 attached to the GitHub Release. PR builds produce an unsigned VST3 artifact.
- Local and CI run the same commands (`flox activate -- task ...`) — no CI-only invocation paths.

## Non-goals

- Linux CI builds (still possible later via the existing Linux container path; out of scope here).
- Cross-platform pixel-bit-equal VRT (baselines pinned to macos-14 arm64 only).
- Self-hosted runners.

---

## Test tiers

### 1. Unit tests (Catch2, in `test/unit/`)

Pure C++ tests with no Doom renderer, no JUCE plugin host. One CMake target `doomviz_unit_tests`. Runs in milliseconds.

Coverage:
- `audio/AudioAnalyzer` — FFT magnitude bins, RMS, envelope follower attack/release, onset trigger threshold.
- `audio/SignalBus` — ring buffer push/pull invariants, atomic MIDI state read/write under a synthetic producer/consumer.
- `audio/MidiHandler` — note on/off, CC, program change parse paths.
- `routing/SignalRouter` + `RouteConfig` — YAML parse, blend modes (replace / add / multiply / max), gain/offset/smoothing.
- `patch/PatchSettingsStore` — round-trip XML serialization, default settings, gain/sprite ID preservation.
- `patch/SpriteCatalog` — `findSpriteById` / `findSpriteByCode` lookups.

### 2. Integration tests (Catch2, in `test/integration/`)

Drive the real `DoomVizProcessor` with a synthetic JUCE `AudioBuffer` and `MidiBuffer`. No editor, no OpenGL. One CMake target `doomviz_integration_tests`.

Coverage:
- `processBlock` does not modify audio data (true pass-through assertion).
- MIDI Program Change `0/1/2` updates `sceneOverride`.
- DAW state save/restore via `getStateInformation` → `setStateInformation` round-trips patch settings byte-for-byte.
- Scene transitions (`KillRoom` → `Spectrum2` → `Analyzer`) do not leak state — verified by snapshotting scene-private members across transitions.
- `Spectrum2Scene` produces non-trivial band amplitudes when fed a known multitone signal.

### 3. End-to-end / visual regression (`test/vrt/`)

The fancy tier. One CMake target `doomviz_vrt_runner` plus a Python comparison driver `test/vrt/run_vrt.py`.

Architecture:
1. `doomviz_vrt_runner <scene-id> <input.wav> <output_dir>` — standalone binary that:
   - Instantiates `DoomVizProcessor` directly (no plugin host wrapper, no OpenGL).
   - Streams a committed PCM file (decoded once from `test/audio/test_dnb.mp3` via ffmpeg and committed under `test/vrt/audio/`) through `processBlock` in fixed 512-sample blocks at 44.1 kHz.
   - Calls the active scene's `update(deltaTime=512/44100)` and `render()` per block.
   - At every Nth block (snapshot cadence — start with N=43, ≈ every 0.5 s), writes the 320×200 indexed framebuffer plus current palette as a PPM into `<output_dir>/frame_NNNN.ppm`.
2. `run_vrt.py` — compares each `output_dir/frame_NNNN.ppm` against `test/vrt/baselines/<scene>/frame_NNNN.ppm`:
   - Bit-exact diff first (passes ⇒ done).
   - On mismatch: write `diffs/frame_NNNN.diff.ppm` (pixel XOR or per-pixel L1 distance, scaled to be visible) and record the failure.
   - At end, emit a JUnit XML report (`vrt-results.xml`) and a contact-sheet HTML (`vrt-report.html`) embedding baseline / actual / diff side-by-side per failing frame.
   - Exits non-zero on any mismatch.
3. Baselines committed under `test/vrt/baselines/<scene>/`. Refresh via `task vrt-update-baselines` (a thin wrapper that runs the runner and copies output to baselines/).

Determinism prerequisites — must be audited and locked down before baselines are committed:
- `juce::Time::getMillisecondCounter()` / `Time::currentTimeMillis()` must not be used by any scene update path. Audit and replace any wall-clock reads with the caller-provided `deltaTime`.
- Doom's `M_Random` is already deterministic (seeded LUT) — no change needed.
- FFT plan: JUCE wraps Apple vDSP on macOS, which is deterministic for fixed input. Pin tests to macos-14 arm64.
- Onset thresholds are floating-point near-equal at boundary frames; snapshot cadence (every 0.5 s) is set so a one-frame timing slip on a single onset doesn't cascade into many failed frames.
- Acidwarp/Vaporwave/Punkrock/Doomtex backgrounds use accumulated `time` driven by `deltaTime` — deterministic given fixed deltaTime.
- Any scene-internal `static` state (e.g. starfield init) must be reset on `init()` — audit `Spectrum2Scene::init`, `Spectrum2Scene::cleanup`.

Scenes covered initially: all three (Kill Room, Analyzer, Doom Spectrum). Spectrum gets an additional VRT pass per Background Vibe (7 vibes × ≈30 frames per ≈15 s of audio).

