## Secrets to provision in GitHub repo settings

For signing:
- `MACOS_CERTIFICATE_P12_BASE64` — base64 of your exported `Developer ID Application: Tristan Mayshark (PHY35R5456)` cert + private key (.p12).
- `MACOS_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD` — the password used at .p12 export.

For notarization (App Store Connect API key path, recommended):
- `AC_API_KEY_ID` — key ID from appstoreconnect.apple.com → Users and Access → Keys.
- `AC_API_ISSUER_ID` — issuer ID from the same page.
- `AC_API_KEY_P8` — full contents of the downloaded `.p8` private key file (one-time download — store carefully).

API-key approach is preferred over app-specific-password because passwords expire (forcing secret rotation) and the API key has finer-grained scope.

