## Reporting & artifacts

- **Pass/fail visibility:** `EnricoMi/publish-unit-test-result-action` posts a comment on the PR summarizing test counts and links to failing cases. Native GitHub Checks UI also lists each ctest case.
- **VRT artifact viewability:** the generated `vrt-report.html` embeds baseline / actual / diff PNGs side-by-side per failing frame. Reviewer downloads the artifact zip, opens the HTML locally — no GitHub Pages dependency. Single-file artifact, ~1–5 MB typical.
- **Build artifacts retention:** GitHub default is 90 days. Acceptable.

---

## Phasing (one PR per phase)

1. **CI skeleton + render_test on CI.** Just `actions/checkout` + flox install + `task build-mac` + `task test` (existing render baseline). Proves the macos-14 runner can build the project. No new tests yet.
2. **Catch2 + unit tests.** Add `extern/Catch2`, `test/unit/`, write tests for AudioAnalyzer / SignalBus / SignalRouter / PatchSettingsStore / SpriteCatalog. Wire into ctest.
3. **Integration tests.** Add `test/integration/`, `processBlock` pass-through + state save/restore + scene transitions.
4. **Determinism audit + VRT runner.** Audit + fix any wall-clock / static-state issues. Land `doomviz_vrt_runner` and `run_vrt.py`. Commit initial baselines (one update-baselines run, eyeball, commit).
5. **VRT in CI.** Wire `task vrt` into the workflow. Upload artifacts + HTML report. Failing baselines block the PR.
6. **Release path.** Add the `release` job, secrets, and `notarize-mac-ci` task. Verify by cutting `v0.1.0` tag.
